  "title": "Assistant IT Manager (Construction Industry)",
  "description": "<p>• Oversee and maintain the company’s IT infrastructure—including servers, LAN/WAN/VPN networks, and site connectivity—to ensure high availability across offices and construction sites.<br>\n• Lead the implementation and support of construction-related technologies (BIM/VDC/VR systems, project management tools, document control platforms, CCTVs) and integrate them with corporate systems such as ERP, HRMS, and IFCA.<br>\n• Manage day-to-day IT helpdesk operations, ensuring timely technical support and providing training to employees where needed.<br>\n• Develop, implement, and enforce IT policies, procedures, and security measures (firewalls, endpoint protection, access controls) to protect sensitive information.<br>\n• Plan and oversee the IT budget, vendor relationships, and service-level agreements for hardware, software licensing, and connectivity services.<br>\n• Evaluate and adopt emerging technologies—such as mobile field reporting and cloud collaboration tools—to improve project efficiency and data accuracy.<br>\n• Oversee routine maintenance, data backups, disaster recovery plans, and business continuity efforts to reduce downtime during system or cybersecurity incidents.<br>\n• Work closely with project teams and department leaders to align IT initiatives with construction workflows and support operational effectiveness.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>We regret only shortlisted candidates will be contacted. All applications will be handled confidentially. By submitting your application, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and disclosure of your personal information to prospective employers.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Wecruit Pte Ltd</p>\n<p>EA License No: 20C0270</p>",
